The Sh1 billion portable clinics lying idle at the National Youth Service (NYS) camp in Miritini area of Mombasa have been vandalised and medical equipment worth millions of shillings stolen. This emerged yesterday during an inspection tour by the National Assembly’s Health committee. MPs were shocked to establish that some of the imported equipment in the multimillion-shilling potable clinics were missing, damaged or had rusted and therefore cannot be used. Cash allocated However despite this, Ministry of Health is demanding to be allocated Sh600 million to transport the 40-foot container clinics to various counties across the nation. The MPs, led by committee deputy chairman  Swarup Mishr, now wants Health Cabinet secretary Sicily Kariuki and the supplier arrested over the tender. He said there was no value for money paid by the government.